<h2>{% trans %}What this module provides{% endtrans %}</h2>
<p>{% trans %}BM Help AI adds an aggregated help page at <code>/admin/help/ai</code> that brings together help topics, legacy <code>hook_help()</code> overviews, and contextual signals. AI is optional and currently represented as a placeholder section.{% endtrans %}</p>

<h3>{% trans %}Key behaviors{% endtrans %}</h3>
<ul>
  <li>{% trans %}Lists all help topics without altering their content or hierarchy.{% endtrans %}</li>
  <li>{% trans %}Surfaces module overviews from <code>hook_help()</code> and explicitly flagged topics.{% endtrans %}</li>
  <li>{% trans %}Builds a situation-aware list using route, roles, and enabled modules as inputs for future relevance scoring.{% endtrans %}</li>
  <li>{% trans %}Separates AI output as non-authoritative, keeping canonical help as the source of truth.{% endtrans %}</li>
</ul>

<p>{% trans %}See the design document topic for architectural goals and extension points.{% endtrans %}</p>
